## Pear Diamond Engagement Ring in White Gold

[![Pear diamond engagement ring with pavé shank in white gold — micro-set accent diamonds running along the band](/images/pear-diamond-engagement-ring-pave-white-gold.avif)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Pear&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)
*Pavé pear diamond engagement ring in white gold — accent diamonds along the shank add sparkle without competing with the pear center stone. **[Browse pavé pear engagement rings →](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Pear&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)***

White gold is the most popular metal choice for pear diamond engagement rings. It provides the platinum visual aesthetic — cool, neutral, white — at a 20–30% lower setting price. The tradeoff: white gold requires rhodium replating every 1–3 years to maintain its white finish. Platinum never requires replating.

For a pear diamond engagement ring worn daily, the replating interval is worth factoring into the total cost of ownership. Three replating sessions over 10 years at $50–$150 each adds $150–$450 to the total cost — still well below the platinum price premium.

**14k vs. 18k white gold for pear engagement rings:**

14k white gold (58.5% gold content) is slightly harder than 18k. For engagement rings worn daily, the higher hardness of 14k makes it marginally more durable. 18k white gold (75% gold) has a richer gold alloy content that some buyers prefer for heirloom pieces. For pear diamond engagement rings specifically, Farzana's default recommendation is 14k white gold as the non-platinum option — harder, more resistant to scratching on the shank, and essentially identical visually.

The Pear Shape Side Stone Halo in white gold at **[$3,570](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/pear-shape-side-stone-diamond-halo-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-310842?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** is the best white-gold pear engagement ring setting on Blue Nile for 1.5ct+ center stones. The pear-specific halo frame accommodates the asymmetrical silhouette correctly, and the 14k white gold construction holds up well for daily wear.

