## How to Buy a Pear Diamond Engagement Ring on Blue Nile

The Blue Nile "Design Your Own Ring" process for a pear diamond engagement ring has four steps, and the order matters:

**Step 1: Choose orientation.** Decide point-up or point-down before selecting a setting. The V-prong placement in the setting is orientation-specific. This decision cannot be undone without a full reset.

**Step 2: Select the setting.** Choose your setting in your preferred metal (all metals are available for all settings). Add it to cart without a center stone first — the design tool will prompt you to "add a diamond" next.

**Step 3: Select the center stone.** Filter by shape (pear), carat weight, cut (Ideal), color (G+ for white gold/platinum; H–I for yellow/rose gold), and clarity (VS2 minimum for eye-clean). Watch the 360° video on every stone shortlisted. Look for: even light return across the full face, a minimal bow-tie shadow, and smooth curvature at the belly.

**Step 4: Confirm V-prong.** Before completing the purchase, confirm with Blue Nile customer service that the selected setting uses a V-prong at the tip of the pear stone. This is standard for pear-specific settings but not always guaranteed for generic solitaire settings used with pear diamonds.

Blue Nile returns are free within 30 days on all unmounted stones and set engagement rings — which provides a practical option to try the finished ring before committing permanently.

